I'll now execute the first tool in the workflow to read the input data using the default file path.

<tool_call>file_operations_reader
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_parser tool to transform the raw data we read into a structured format. Since the parser requires a source parameter, I'll use the same input file path as before.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json"
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the final tool in the workflow to filter the data. Since the filter tool doesn't have a source parameter and only optional options, I'll use the default empty object.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
